ative atmosphere.","Lay the groundwork for establishing a constructive feedback and code review culture. Beyond simply patching up the current issue, you should propose a draft of 'Code Review Guidelines for Mutual Respect' to prevent similar conflicts from recurring in the future. This will be a long-term solution contributing to the entire team's development, not just individual growth."}	You genuinely reconcile with Senior Developer Kim Cheol-min, developing an even stronger trust relationship than before. Under your collaborative efforts, an improved architecture is applied, and the feature is perfectly implemented by the Friday deadline, leaving a deep impression on the CTO by demonstrating the team's growth and problem-solving capabilities.	You formally apologize, and Senior Developer Kim Cheol-min accepts it and returns to work. Technically, a compromise is found to maintain the broad outline of the original design, while incorporating some of your suggestions, and the deadline is met through additional weekend work. The team atmosphere remains somewhat awkward, but work proceeds normally.	A formal reconciliation occurs with the CTO's intervention, and development resumes according to PM Park Su-jin's proposed mediation. However, fundamental emotional rifts remain, and the project is delayed by 2-3 days before being handed over to the QA team. An uncomfortable atmosphere still lingers within the team.	Attempts at dialogue lead to a recurrence of the emotional conflict, and Senior Developer Kim Cheol-min officially declares his withdrawal from the project. The project is halted indefinitely, the CTO is forced to reconfigure the team, and official personnel action against you is considered. Team trust is completely shattered.	ko	[{"goal": "He wants his professionalism and seniority to be respected. He expects the junior developer to formally acknowledge his inappropriate attitude and apologize for this incident. Furthermore, he wishes for his existing code to b