, that for important modules, seniors should lead and new employees should assist, as this is efficient for risk management. Senior Researcher Lee Su-jin (ISFJ) is showing a passive attitude, unwilling to engage in conflict between the Department Head's decision and the new employee's awkward position, and Project Manager Park Ji-won (INFJ) is concerned that this situation could hinder the team's potential but, lacking direct authority over personnel, is carefully observing.\n\nIf this role ambiguity issue is not resolved within two weeks, serious setbacks will occur in module development due to duplicated work, responsibility avoidance, and communication confusion. This will ultimately lead to a delay in the entire 'Project N-Core' schedule, resulting in the worst possible outcome: billions of won in opportunity cost losses and ceding market preemption opportunities to competitors. Personally, it will critically impact your initial impressions and performance evaluations, making it very difficult to establish a foundation for your future career within the company.\n\nTherefore, you must act as a proactive problem-solver in this scenario. You must not merely express dissatisfaction but logically persuade Department Head Kim Dong-hyun of your position, minimizing his psychological resistance based on the SCARF model and TA (Transactional Analysis) theory. Understanding the Department Head's decision-making style (ISTJ) and presenting data and concrete alternatives instead of emotional appeals to achieve a mutual 'Win-Win' new role distribution plan is the core objective of this task. Your communication skills and strategic thinking will determine the success or failure of the project and your future.	The incident occurred yesterday at 9 AM during the 'Project N-Core' weekly meeting. While reviewing the project's progress, Department Head Kim Dong-hyun displayed the organizational chart on the screen and abruptly stated: "For efficiency, Senior Researcher Lee Su-jin will handle the core logic of the data module, and the new employee will be responsible for data validation and auxiliary development. Adjust the specifics as you proceed." This statement publicly demoted your role to 'auxiliary' and posed a threat to your Status. When you tried to say, "I have a question regarding the specific scope of work," the Department Head waved his hand, cutting you off with, "We don't have time for that now; let's discuss it later." This left your role, responsibilities, and reporting structure all in an uncertain state (threatening Certainty), making you feel at a loss as to where to even begin. After the meeting, colleagues murmured in confusion about whom to ask regarding related tasks, and Senior Researcher Lee Su-jin avoided eye contact with you and left. Within the organization, rumors are circulating that Department Head Kim has made several unilateral decisions before, adding a layer of political complexity that requires you to be very cautious in approaching this issue.	New Employee / Core Development Team / New Hire (3 months in) / Responsible for the successful development of the assigned 'data collection and pre-processing module'. Must proactively resolve the current role ambiguity issue, re-establish clear R&R through discussions with stakeholders including the Department Head, and contribute to project success.	t	f	\N	2026-01-25 02:02:26.408023	2026-01-25 02:02:26.408023	Only two weeks remain until the board demonstration of the project prototype. Detailed design for each module must be completed by next Monday, and the final role distribution based on this must be finalized by this Friday to meet the development schedule. With competitor 'MiraeTech' announcing a similar system launch early next month, any schedule delay would mean market failure.	For you personally, successful performance in this project is directly linked to your first performance review and is a crucial opportunity to build a foundation for your future care