th and potential realization of individual team members are key to long-term success. I see the current role ambiguity as a serious problem that stifles the new employee's motivation and hinders team synergy. I believe that only by resolving this issue can the project truly succeed.", "position": "PM (Project Manager)", "tradeoff": "I do not have direct authority to intervene in the development team's personnel matters or R&R. Therefore, I must operate within limits that do not infringe upon the Department Head's authority. However, if the new employee proactively seeks my help with a constructive alternative for problem-solving, I will fulfill my role as an enabler, such as arranging a meeting or providing data on past project failures. I am a facilitator, not a solver.", "personaId": "infj", "department": "Project Management Office"}]	{"Conflict Management","Negotiation and Persuasion","SCARF Model Application","Problem Solving","Strategic Communication"}	f
